cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

This paper is about factorised relational databases and their query engine. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses algorithms for query optimization and evaluation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper mentions boosting query performance, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper suggest that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves evaluating performance metrics.
